Reasoning: 
1. cs.CL (Computation and Language) - The paper focuses on the emergence of a written language system through multi-agent cooperation, which falls under the scope of natural language processing and language evolution. 
2. cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) - The paper aims to develop a general AI by studying the emergence of a writing system, which is a crucial aspect of human communication. 
3. cs.LG (Machine Learning) - The paper uses a referential game setup with two agents, which involves learning and coordination, and thus falls under the scope of machine learning. 
4. cs.SD (Sound) - Although the paper does not explicitly mention sound, the emergence of a writing system can be seen as a form of encoding and decoding information, which is related to sound and speech processing. 
5. cs.CC (Computational Complexity) - While the paper does not focus on computational complexity, the study of emergent writing systems can have implications for the complexity of communication and language processing in artificial agents.
